(In reply to Cristina Horotan [:chorotan] from comment #22)
> Backed out for causing mochitest failures on test_group_zoom-2.html

Bug 1776966 is the intermittent Bug for this test series. Landing the pref may have made it into a perma-fail. This test runs several helper subtests. The relevant timeout is in `helper_zoom_after_gpu_process_restart.html`, which [emits one `ok` result](https://searchfox.org/firefox-main/rev/dc1c78e9c37aba6ed05a4ec47c4bfcb16f57b51d/gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/helper_zoom_after_gpu_process_restart.html#14) and then times out, presumably in this section:
```
let promise = TestUtils.topicObserved("compositor-reinitialized");
gfxInfo.killGPUProcessForTests();
await promise;
```
When I test locally, this manifests as a failure to focus the test window. I'll try to improve behavior in this test, then attempt a re-land of the pref flip.

